{{Infobox person | name = Gaël Duval | image = Gael_Duval_(officiel).jpg | caption = Gaël Duval | birth_name = Gaël Duval | birth_place = [[Caen]], [[Normandy]], [[France]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | nationality = [[France|French]] | years_active = from 1998 to now | known_for = [[Mandriva Linux]] creator, [[Mandriva]] co-founder | website = {{url|https://www.indidea.org/gael/blog/}} }}
'''Gaël Duval''' (born 1973) is a French entrepreneur. In July 1998, he created Mandrake Linux (now [[Mandriva Linux]]), a [[Linux distribution]] originally based on [[Red Hat Linux]] and [[KDE]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=CUcbyVTztecC&pg=PA309&dq=isbn:0738206709+mandrake&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiK1uDe2LrSAhXDuRoKHTfBCr0Q6AEIHDAA#v=onepage&q=isbn:0738206709%20mandrake&f=false|title=Rebel Code: Linux and the Open Source Revolution|last=Moody|first=Glyn|date=2002-01-01|publisher=Basic Books|isbn=0738206709|language=en}}</ref> He was also a co-founder of MandrakeSoft (now merged in [[Mandriva]]) with Jacques Le Marois and Frédéric Bastok.
Gaël Duval was responsible for communication in the Mandriva management team until he was laid off by the company in March 2006, in a round of cost-cutting. Duval suspected part of the reason for his dismissal was disagreement with management over the company's future strategy, resulting in a lawsuit against the company.<ref>[http://www.indidea.org/gael/en/fired-message.php La page perso de Gaël Duval, créateur de Mandrake Linux/Mandriva Linux, co-fondateur de Mandrakesoft/Mandriva - FAQ Mandriva<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071222034630/http://www.indidea.org/gael/en/fired-message.php |date=2007-12-22 }}</ref><ref>[http://club.mandriva.com/xwiki/bin/Main/interview-fbancilhon-2006-03 Interview of François Bancilhon, CEO of Mandriva<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071220045625/http://club.mandriva.com/xwiki/bin/Main/interview-fbancilhon-2006-03 |date=2007-12-20 }}</ref>
{{As of|2006}}, Duval is Chairman and Chief Technology Officer at [[Ulteo]].<ref>[http://www.news.com/8301-10784_3-9832336-7.html?tag=newsmap Ulteo brings OpenOffice to Web browser | Tech news blog - CNET News.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The company is bought by AZNetwork group in 2015.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}
In 2016, he co-founded NFactory.io, an incubator-accelerator of "startups".<ref>[https://www.ouest-france.fr/normandie/caen-14000/la-normandie-est-une-belle-carte-jouer-4711627 « La Normandie est une belle carte à jouer »]</ref>
In November 2017, Gael Duval has created mobile platform /e/<ref>[https://www.indidea.org/gael/blog/leaving-apple-and-google-e-is-the-symbol-for-my-data-is-my-data/ Leaving Apple and Google: /e/ is the symbol for “my data is MY data” — Gaël Duval (news, mandrake, /e/ my data is my data...)]</ref> (/e/ is the symbol for "My data is MY data"), which is based on AOSP as a fork of [[LineageOS]] along with a set of online services such as search, cloud drive, email. This new mobile ecosystem, released as a first beta on September 12th, 2018 is focusing on user's data privacy, and isn't using any Google service <ref>[https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/290746744/eelo-a-mobile-os-and-web-services-in-the-public-in eelo, a mobile OS and web-services, in the public interest by Gaël Duval — Kickstarter]</ref><ref>[https://www.indidea.org/gael/blog/leaving-apple-google-eelo-odyssey-introduction/ Leaving Apple and Google : my «eelo odyssey» — Introduction — Gaël Duval (À propos, news, mandrake, eelo…)]</ref><ref>[https://www.zdnet.com/article/eelo-a-google-less-android-alternative-emerges/ Eelo: A Google-less Android alternative emerges | ZDNet]</ref><ref>[https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=Eelo-Mobile-Linux-OS Eelo: The Latest Linux Mobile Attempt, Led By Mandrake's Founder - Phoronix]</ref><ref>[https://fossbytes.com/eelo-mobile-os-open-source-android-alternative/ eelo: An Open Source Android-alternative Being Developed By Mandrake Linux Creator], '''FossBytes'''</ref><ref>[https://liliputing.com/2017/12/mandrake-linux-founder-developing-eelo-open-source-mobile-os-android-without-google-apps-services.html Mandrake Linux founder is developing eelo: an open source mobile OS (Android without the Google apps and services) - Liliputing]</ref><ref>[https://hackernoon.com/leaving-apple-google-e-first-beta-is-here-89e39f492c6f Leaving Apple & Google: /e/ first beta is here! — Gaël Duval]</ref>. In 2018, Duval created e Foundation for /e/.<ref>[https://e.foundation/efoundation/ eFoundation — /e/]</ref><ref>[https://www.indidea.org/gael/blog/announcing-e-foundation-for-eelo/ Announcing «e Foundation» for eelo — Gaël Duval (news, mandrake, /e/ my data is my data…)]</ref>
==Education==
Duval is a graduate of the [[University of Caen Lower Normandy|Caen University]] in [[France]], where he studied networks and documentary applications{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}.
