{{Infobox YouTube personality | name = Hjallis | image = Hjallis Harkimo.jpg | caption = Harry "Hjallis" Harkimo in 2011. | channel_name = Hjallis | views = | birth_name = | nationality = Finnish | occupation = Entrepreneurship, Member of parliament | origin = [[Helsinki, Finland]] | website = {{URL|www.hjallis.fi}} | years_active = 2017–present | genre = [[society]], [[politics]], [[business]], [[entertainment]], [[sport]] | subscribers = 51 thousand+ | network = | silver_year = | gold_year = | diamond_year = |stats_update=August 11, 2018| silver_button = | gold_button = | diamond_button = }}
'''Harry Juhani "Hjallis" Harkimo''' (born 2 November 1953 in [[Helsinki]]) is a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[businessman]], YouTuber<ref>https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCMIeHLvwrUnq7U55HCuiEeA</ref>, sportsperson and a member of the Finnish Parliament. He was elected representing the [[National Coalition Party]]; however, in 2018 he left the party and founded new political movement, [[Liike Nyt]]. Harkimo is the [[chairman of the board]] of the [[Helsinki]]-based ice-hockey team [[Jokerit]].<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Jokerit |url=http://www.jokerit.com/index.php?id=35 |title=Jokerit information in English |accessdate=August 30, 2010}}</ref> He is also the developer of the team's home arena, [[Hartwall Areena]], and an investor in sports. Harkimo has also hosted Finnish version of ''[[The Apprentice (TV series)|The Apprentice]]'' in 2009–2013.<ref>[http://www.hs.fi/viihde/artikkeli/Harkimo+etsii+Diilin+avulla+vet%C3%A4j%C3%A4%C3%A4+nyt+Hanko-projektilleen/1135252432957 Helsingin Sanomat: Harkimo etsii Diilin avulla vetäjää nyt Hanko-projektilleen] (in Finnish).</ref> In October 2017, Harkimo started to make YouTube videos where he speaks about politics, business, sports etc.
Harkimo was elected to the parliament in 2015, gaining 11,416 votes in the elections.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tulospalvelu.vaalit.fi/E-2015/fi/val02.html |title=Valitut ehdokkaat Uudenmaan vaalipiiri |publisher=Ministry of Justice |accessdate=9 May 2015}}</ref>
He has also been a professional sailor and a sports manager. In 1986–1987 he took part of round-the-world single-handed yacht race [[VELUX 5 Oceans Race|BOC Challenge]] and finished third.
==Personal life== Early 2000s, Hjallis divorced his [[Parliament of Finland|member-of-parliament]]-wife [[Leena Harkimo]] and married younger member-of-parliament [[Merikukka Forsius-Harkimo]]. Harry Harkimo and Merikukka Forsius-Harkimo divorced after one year of marriage.
Harkimo has been [[vegetarian]] since start of 2018.<ref>{{cite|url=http://www.iltalehti.fi/politiikka/201804222200894860_pi.shtml|title=Hjallis Harkimo ryhtyi kasvissyöjäksi ja laihtui - ”Tuntuu tosi hyvältä”|}}</ref>
