{{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = | name = Muquim Ahmed | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = 200px | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = bn | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1954|9|1|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Sylhet]], [[East Bengal]] (now [[Bangladesh]]) | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | residence = [[Shadwell]], [[London Borough of Tower Hamlets|Tower Hamlets]], [[London]], [[England]] | nationality = [[United Kingdom|British]] | other_names = | citizenship = | education = [[Industrial engineering|Production Engineering]] | alma_mater = | occupation = [[Entrepreneur]] | years_active = | employer = | organization = | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = Café Naz restaurants | style = | home_town = | salary = | net_worth = | height = | weight = | television = | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | awards = | website = | footnotes = }}
'''Muquim Ahmed''' (born 1 September 1954) is a [[Bangladesh]]i-born [[United Kingdom|British]] [[entrepreneur]]. He is thought to be the first [[Brick Lane]] millionaire.{{Citation needed|date = April 2016}}
==Biography== Ahmed arrived in [[East End of London|East]] [[London]] in the early 1970s, aged 19, to study [[Engineering]] with the intention of returning to join the family business in [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="times1">{{cite news |title=Focus: Immigrant Britain |url=http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/article732392.ece |location= |newspaper=[[The Sunday Times]] |date=19 February 2006 |accessdate=26 April 2009}}</ref>
Having invested £2 million in a bakery and a ready meals factory in [[South West (London sub region)|South West London]], Ahmed, 55, is building a food manufacturing leg to his property and restaurant portfolio. Best known for his work in transforming the Brick Lane area of East London, later helped his father export goods from Britain and the Netherlands to Bangladesh. He diversified into property and was a millionaire at 26. He has a £30m property portfolio while his ''Café Naz'' chain of restaurants turns over about £3.5 million a year. His other interests include a travel agency.<ref name="times1" />
Ahmed is also a fellow of [[Queen Mary, University of London|The University of London]].<ref name="times1"/>
