{{BLP sources|date=February 2012}} {{Infobox person | image = | name = Richard Broadbridge | birth_date = | birth_place = Fiji | occupation = Managing Director [[Mai TV]] }}
'''Richard Broadbridge''' leads the [[Skylite Productions]] Fiji operations and is also Managing Director of Fiji's [[free-to-air]] network [[Mai TV]]. Skylite Productions Fiji is a shareholder of MAI TV and is currently contracted to provide the station its local content. Richard is also Managing Director of Stockwell Limited, which has shares in MAI TV Fiji, Mailife Fiji and also Skylite Productions Fiji.
==Biography== He studied at [[Sacred Heart College, Auckland]]. In Fiji, he studied at the [[Marist Brothers High School, Fiji|Marist Brothers High School]].
He started his career in 1993 as a journalist with the [[Fiji Broadcasting Corporation]] Limited (formerly Radio Fiji).<ref name="The Fiji Times">{{cite news|last=Singh|first=Monika|title=How Richard made his mark in the field of journalism|url=http://www.fijitimes.com/story.aspx?ref=archive&id=69754|accessdate=3 May 2013|newspaper=The Fiji Times|date=September 2, 2007}}</ref> He is also a former [[Fiji TV]] employee and [[Television journalist|TV Journalist]]. He was the first local reporter when Fiji TV started Fiji One News in April 1994. He resigned from Fiji TV in 2001.
