'''Serhiy Makarov''' ({{lang-uk|Сергій Макаров}}; born 8 June 1977 in [[Mariupol|Zhdanov]], [[Donetsk Oblast]]) is a Ukrainian sports functionary, a president of the [[Professional Football League of Ukraine]] (PFL).

==Biography==
Makarov graduated the Donetsk State Technical University in management of foreign economic activity and later information computer systems and technologies.

At least since 2009 Makarov worked for PFL, at first as a director of information and analytical center, and later since 2010 as an executive director. During that period Makarov received a certification in sports management under the programs НУФВСУ and CIES which were provided by FFU along with FIFA.

On 27 June 2014 Makarov won the presidential election of PFL<ref>Ushakov, O. ''[http://amsport.com.ua/news/prezident-pfl-sergey-makarov-otvechaet-na-voprosy The PFL president Serhiy Makarov answers the question (Президент ПФЛ Сергей Макаров отвечает на вопросы)]''. Amatorskyi sport.</ref> becoming its fifth president.

